item.title: Rachel add a quote by Charlotte Brontë
item.description: "I am no bird; and no net ensnares me: I am a free human being with an independent will." -- Charlotte Brontë

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Abraham Lincoln
item.description: "I am in favor of animal rights as well as human rights. That is the way of a whole human being." -- Abraham Lincoln

item.title: Rachel add a quote by W.B. Yeats
item.description: "For he would be thinking of love Till the stars had run away And the shadows eaten the moon." -- W.B. Yeats

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Stephen King
item.description: "Books are a uniquely portable magic." -- Stephen King

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Pablo Neruda
item.description: "I love you without knowing how, or when, or from where. I love you simply, without problems or pride: I love you in this way because I do not know any other way of loving but this, in which there is no I or you, so intimate that your hand upon my chest is my hand, so intimate that when I fall asleep your eyes close." -- Pablo Neruda

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Carl Sandburg
item.description: "Time is the coin of your life. You spend it. Do not allow others to spend it for you." -- Carl Sandburg

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Harlan Ellison
item.description: "You are not entitled to your opinion. You are entitled to your <i>informed</i> opinion. No one is entitled to be ignorant." -- Harlan Ellison
